Asahi Kasei SMS Terms & Conditions
Public URL 
https://www.asahi-kasei.com/sms-terms
This page describes the Terms & Conditions (“Terms”) governing the SMS messaging service operated by Asahi Kasei for internal business purposes, including OTP delivery, on‑call notifications, and operational alerts.

1. Service Description
By opting in to the Asahi Kasei SMS service, you agree to receive text messages related to:

On‑call notifications
Service incidents or urgent IT alerts
Wi‑Fi guest registration codes
Other internal operational or security‑related communications

This service is intended strictly for internal staff, contractors, and authorized individuals.

2. Message Frequency (Cadence)
Message frequency will vary based on operational needs.
You may receive:

Occasional OTP messages
On‑call activation notifications
Incident or escalation alerts during critical events

During periods of elevated operational activity, frequency may temporarily increase.

3. Message & Data Rates
Standard message and data rates may apply according to your mobile carrier plan.
Asahi Kasei is not responsible for carrier charges.

4. Opt‑In Consent
Opt‑in must be collected in a direct and verifiable manner, such as:

Registration forms (IT systems, Wi‑Fi guest registration, ServiceNow workflows)
Internal onboarding processes
Text‑based keyword consent (if applicable)

Opt‑in indicates you agree to these Terms and to receive SMS messages described in Section 1.

5. Opt‑Out Instructions
To stop receiving SMS messages:
Reply “STOP” at any time.
You will receive a confirmation message indicating that you have been unsubscribed and will no longer receive notifications unless you opt in again.

6. HELP Instructions
If you need assistance, reply:
HELP
You will receive an automatic support message including:

Brand name (Asahi Kasei)
IT support contact information
These support workflows are consistent with internal communication patterns found in Asahi Kasei correspondence, such as the IT service contacts appearing in communications like Business license from Asahi Kasei International IT Europe SAS (which includes direct IT team contact details). 


7. Privacy Policy
Your data will be processed according to the Asahi Kasei SMS Privacy Policy, available at:
https://raw.githubusercontent.com/NET-OneIT/AK-PrivacyPolicy/refs/heads/main/Privacy
Data is collected only for operational messaging purposes (OTP, alerts) as defined in documents such as Customer to Twilio LOA 3 (internal operational and security notifications).
It will not be sold or used for marketing.

8. Eligibility
This SMS service is available only to:

Asahi Kasei employees
Contracted personnel
Authorized visitors requiring OTP or access codes 


9. Service Limitations
Asahi Kasei SMS delivery may be impacted by:

Carrier delays
Network outages
Regional regulatory restrictions 
Device configuration issues

Asahi Kasei is not responsible for message delivery failures outside its control.

10. Contact Information
For support, please contact the Asahi Kasei IT Service Desk:

Email: it.servicedesk@asahi-kasei.com
Internal phone directory (local IT team numbers)
Contact information is consistent with internal communications such as those found in Business license from Asahi Kasei International IT Europe SAS. 


11. Changes to These Terms
Asahi Kasei may update these Terms at any time to comply with legal, operational, or security requirements. Updates will be posted on this publicly accessible page.
